{"id":"285924191_Crystal_Structure_Refinement_A_Crystallographer's_Guide_to_SHELXL","abstract":"This book covers advanced aspects of practical crystal structure refinement, focusing on practical problems in the everyday life of a crystallographer. After an introduction to SHELXL in the first chapter, the second chapter provides a brief survey of crystal structure refinement. The next few chapters address the various aspects of structure refinement, from the treatment of hydrogen atoms to the assignment of atom types, to disorder, to non-crystallographic symmetry and twinning. One chapter is dedicated to the refinement of macromolecular structures and two shorter chapters deal with structure validation. In most chapters, the book gives refinement examples, based on the program SHELXL, describing every problem in detail.","authors":["Peter MÃ¼ller","Regine Herbst-Irmer","A.L. Spek","T.R. Schneider"],"meta":["January 2010","DOI:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780198570769.001.0001"],"references":["239670713_Atomic_Motions_in_Molecular_Crystals_from_Diffraction_Measurements","239255512_On_structure_refinement_using_data_from_a_twinned_crystal","12968488_17_A_Structure_of_the_stabilized_REIv_mutant_T39K_Application_of_local_NCS_restraints","12775962_Protein_titration_in_a_crystal_state","12393846_Application_and_comparison_of_different_tests_on_twinning_by_merohedry","12250972_Tetrameric_indium_trichloride_a_new_modification_of_a_widely_used_compound","11240012_Recent_Advances_in_Atomic_Resolution_Protein_Crystallography","7999209_The_170_angstrom_X-ray_crystal_structure_of_Mycobacterium_tuberculosis_phosphoglycerate_mutase","272134793_Synthesis_and_Structures_of_Me_3_Si_3_CAlF_2_2_m_-OLi_2_THF_4_and_LiMe_3_Si_3_CAlF_3_THF_3_LiFTHF","259946594_Can_X-ray_crystal_structure_analysis_decide_between_twinning_by_pseudo-merohedry_and_statistical_distribution_in_YBa2Cu3O7","244748059_The_average_atomic_volume_and_density_of_proteins","244650144_A_test_for_rigid-body_vibrations_based_on_a_ge